# Page motion infrastructure

Every interactive or decorative surface on the demo page **and** every new
element inside the component Shadow DOM must participate in the motion system.
This is production-grade polish — not optional flair.

## Source of truth

| Layer | Role |
| --- | --- |
| `demo/motion/page-motion.css` | Demo chrome motion tokens, keyframes, transitions |
| `demo/motion/page-motion.ts` | Scroll reveal, theme flash, validation/resize pulses |
| `src/styles.ts` | Component motion (`--fc-transition`, card stagger, hovers) |

## Required motion tokens (demo)

Define on `:root` in `page-motion.css` — never hard-code durations in rules:

- `--page-motion-ease-out`, `--page-motion-ease-spring`, `--page-motion-ease-smooth`
- `--page-motion-duration-instant` … `--page-motion-duration-reveal`
- `--page-motion-stagger`

Component equivalent: `--fc-transition`, `--fc-ease-out`, `--fc-ease-spring`,
`--fc-stagger` in `src/styles.ts`.

## Rules for every new UI element

1. **Enter** — fade/slide/scale on first paint or scroll (`motion-reveal` +
   `is-revealed`, or component `fc-*-enter` keyframes with stagger).
2. **Hover / focus** — lift, shadow, colour, or micro-transform under
   `@media (prefers-reduced-motion: no-preference)`.
3. **Active / pressed** — slightly reduced lift (tactile feedback).
4. **State change** — animate pills, validation panels, and loading indicators
   (pop, shake, pulse — pick one appropriate to semantics).
5. **Focus-visible** — always pair motion with a ring; never motion-only affordances.

## Accessibility (non-negotiable)

- Wrap decorative transforms and transitions in
  `@media (prefers-reduced-motion: no-preference)`.
- Under `prefers-reduced-motion: reduce`, demo CSS sets near-zero durations;
  component CSS must set `animation: none` and `transition: none` on animated
  nodes (see `src/styles.ts` reduce block).
- Do not gate keyboard focus or content visibility on animation completion.
- `npm run test:e2e` reduced-motion spec must stay green (`transition-duration: 0s` on cards).

## Adding demo sections

1. Add `motion-reveal` to the section — scroll reveal is automatic via
   `initPageMotion()`.
2. Style with `--page-motion-*` tokens only.
3. Wire stateful feedback through helpers in `page-motion.ts` when applicable.

## Adding component markup

1. Extend `--fc-*` motion tokens if needed (document in `styles.ts` header).
2. Add enter/hover/focus/active animations in the `prefers-reduced-motion:
   no-preference` block.
3. Mirror disables in the `reduce` block.

## Do not

- Import animation libraries (Framer, GSAP, etc.) — CSS + minimal TS only.
- Autoplay infinite motion on critical reading paths without subtle amplitude.
- Use `transition: all` — list properties explicitly.
- Skip motion on “boring” elements (labels, pills, code chips, footer links).
